<h3><b>Step 1</b>: Installing The Requirements & The Quote Linux Launcher</h3>
<p class="text-center">Open your console/terminal and type the following:</p>

<div class="text-center">
    <p style="background-color: dimgray; color: lightskyblue;">curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Quote-Bot/Quote-Scripts/master/get.sh -o get.sh</p>
    <p style="background-color: dimgray; color: lightskyblue;">sh get.sh</p>
</div>
<p class="text-center">What <a style="background-color: dimgray; color: lightskyblue;">get.sh</a> does is, it will install <b>Python</b>, <b>Git</b> and <b>dos2unix</b> if they are not already installed and then download Quote Linux Launcher.</p>
<p class="text-center">After <a style="background-color: dimgray; color: lightskyblue;">get.sh</a> has executed and self-eliminated, your terminal will show something along the lines of what the picture below shows. From there, move on to <b>Step 2</b>.</p>
<div class="text-center">
    <img class="img-fluid" src="~/wwwroot/get.sh completed.png" />
</div>

<hr />

<h3><b>Step 2</b>: Installing Quote</h3>
<p class="text-center">We at Quote have designed a special launcher, better than the one we had before, for the sake of convenience.</p>
<p class="text-center">Start the launcher by typing the following:</p>
<div class="text-center" style="background-color: dimgray; color: lightskyblue;">
    <p>sh quote_launcher.sh</p>
</div>
<p class="text-center">Once you have ran the launcher, you will see the following menu:</p>
<div class="text-center">
    <img class="img-fluid" src="~/wwwroot/quote launcher menu.png" />
</div>
<p class="text-center">Select option 2 to download <b>Quote</b>.</p>

